{
  "texts": [
    "Deterministic AnalysisThe deterministic category relates to systems where hardware and software resources, given a specific input and initial state, generate an output within a specified timeframe.",
    "DTA aims to achieve time predictability by promoting hardware and software designs that ensure deterministic execution times, thereby producing provably safe WCET estimates [40].Gustafsson et al. [41] investigate the impact of Control Flow Charts (CFCs), such as loops and conditional branches, on WCET estimates, emphasizing the influence of software structure on execution time.",
    "Their methods for analyzing control flow paths within software highlights the intricate challenges inherent in WCET analysis and provides advanced analytical tools, enhancing the understanding of execution time factors in real-time systems.",
    "Building on this foundation, the technique proposed by Grebant et al. [42] analyze binary code to produce a WCET formula dependent on procedure arguments by transforming Control Flow Graph (CFG) into Control-Flow Trees (CFT) and using polyhedra-based abstract interpretation to infer input conditionals.",
    "In the context of WCET analysis, polyhedra are used as an abstract domain to represent program invariants."
  ]
}